comments: White (CHI) maintains legal guarding position defending Leonard's (LAC) drive to the basket.
Williams (LAC) cleanly strips the ball from White (CHI).  Any contact is considered incidental.
White (CHI) makes incidental foot to ball contact as he engages for the loose ball.
Morris Sr. (LAC) makes marginal contact to LaVine (CHI) with a bent forearm against his side defending his drive to the basket.
Leonard (LAC) cleanly deflects the pass to Williams' (CHI) in the post.
Batum (LAC) and Temple (CHI) engage and disengage with one another for the loose ball.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the review of the foul called on Leonard (LAC) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful.  Leonard (LAC) avoids making any illegal contact as he reaches in defending Williams (CHI).
Williams (LAC) establishes legal position firming up in Williams' (CHI) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
White (CHI) makes marginal contact to Leonard (LAC) defending his driving shot attempt.
Temple (CHI) makes incidental contact to Leonard (LAC) after his shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Young (CHI) and George (LAC) engage and disengage off ball with one another for the loose ball.
George (LAC) briefly places his hand against Young's (CHI) hip during the screen and quickly slides his hand off.
Leonard (LAC) slightly extends his arm against Williams' (CHI) during the screen and he is able to move through the marginal contact.
White (CHI) makes contact with George (LAC) that affects his FOM.
Beverley (LAC) avoids making contact with LaVine (CHI) as he kicks out as part of his natural shooting motion defending his jump shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
George (LAC) maintains legal guarding position defending Temple's (CHI) drive to the basket and absorbs the contact.
